  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Verification task to ensure that the functional safety concept is consistent and compliant with the safety goals.&lt;br />&#xD;
    This task needs to be carried out in accordance with&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;ISO 26262, volume 8, clause 9&amp;nbsp;and is shown&#xD;
    in&amp;nbsp; the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/capabilitypatterns/8.9%20Verification%20Planning_831C2385.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_91quQZEZEeCUs8vNyweFYw&quot;>8.9 Verification Planning&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;task.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If it can be shown that the Item complies to the functional safety requirements then the item also complies with the&#xD;
    safety goals, in this case it is possible that a traceability argument can be used.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The&amp;nbsp;verification report is captured as part of&amp;nbsp;the functional safety concept.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To ensure that the functional safety concept is consistent and compliant with the safety goals.</purpose>
